data.text:
Agnes Louise Dresser OBITUARY

Agnes ‘Aggie’ Louise Dresser Went to be with the Lord the afternoon of February 2, 2009 in San Jose, CA. She was born in Kenosha, WI on December 6, 1928. She loved knitting, dancing, doing arts and crafts, listening to bagpipes and baking her famous shortbread. Her loving nature and artistic talent will be missed by all. She is preceded in death by her husband, Bill. She is survived by her 4 sons, Will, Rick and his wife Fran, Brian and Rob. Grandchildren Brian Jr., Michelle and her husband Kenny, Chris, Kyle, Jenny and Emily and great-grandchild Emma, 3 sisters Christine, Bonnie and Donna and a long list of friends. A memorial service will be held February 7, 2009, 2:30 pm at South Valley Community Church, 8095 Kelton Ave., Gilroy, CA.
